title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Thames .32 Nickel Revolver
postcontent: Rare Thames Arms, nickel finish, double action revolver. Last Pat. Sept. 30, 1902. Serial# 3591 on frame and cylinder. In .32 S&W caliber. Condition very good, top break, auto eject. Original nickel finish worn in spots but generally very good. Original case hardening still visible on the hammer and triggerguard. Excellent original grips. Very tight lock up and functions very well. Here is what I have been able to glean about Thames Arms from the internet: The Thames Arms Company was originallyincorporated as The Thames Chain & Stamping Company on August 28, 1896. On September 21, 1900 the name was changed to The Thames Arms Company. They sold exact copies of the Hopkins& Allen revolvers and therefore it can be believed that Thames Arms Company was created to sell Hopkins & Allen made guns to other than Merwin, Hulbert & Co. Anyway, Thames Arms Company figured already as of 1885 on some top break revolvers and on some solid frame XL revolvers of H&A. Therefore its origin was likely a trademark of Hopkins & Allen. One more argument is that they utilized the J. Boland (assigned to H&A) and G.W. Cilley's patents as well as of much other patents granted to H&A or its stuff.

title: For Sale:  RWS Model 54 Air king .177 with Hawk 4x12  Air gun scope 475. or trade
postcontent:
This Rifle is in very good condition.Has had about 300 shots through it.It is a tack driver.

The RWS 54 Air King is a recoilless sidelever rifle based on the action of the RWS 48/52 series. By floating the action on rails, RWS takes the rifle's powerful recoil and significantly reduces the amount you feel. It also enhances accuracy, because the pellet exits the barrel before spring vibration is transmitted to it.

Our .177-cal. RWS 54 Air King has the TO5 trigger. The .22-cal. model has the TO6 trigger. Both are 2-stage adjustable triggers and have an excellent reputation.

The 54 is dressed up in a Monte Carlo beech stock with a raised cheekpiece. For better control, RWS added checkering to the grip and forearm. The changes in the stock configuration make an already-great gun even better. Truly, this is a competitor's dream come true! Loading is done through a sliding breech mechanism. Like the 48 and 52, this rifle can be used for field target, plinking, hunting, target shooting and spinners. This sidelever spring-piston rifle is popular among airgunners who truly want to win at whatever they do! To get the most accuracy from this powerhouse, mount a scope. It'll come in handy, whether you're shooting at field targets or quarry.

postcontent:
Think before you even contact too good to be true deals.
 Google Images is amazing and you can search for similar photos. 
 Use google images and do a photo search with the image URL from here.
 You'll see where this scammer has been posting the listings all over including additional listings here.

 Scammers also setup FAKE escrow sites so as a buyer ALWAYS FIND ONE never use their suggestion.

 Still want to buy the item and unsure if it's real? Have the seller take a custom photo with a newspaper leaning on the item or with their hand somewhere specific on the item just to verify they have the item.

 If they ask you to Western Union, MoneyPak, MoneyGram, or escrow in a site they tell you for a deposit or payment your money is GONE.

I have a Kel Tec P3AT in great condition that I'd like to trade or maybe sell.

Its in great shape and has a chromed and polished slide and barrel. Been fired very little, comes with one Mec Gar magazine and its box. These guns can not be beat in size and weight, they weigh only 11 oz's loaded and is one of those guns that you WILL forget you're carrying in your pocket. Say what you will about Kel Tec's but the trigger is far superior to a Ruger LCP's, smooth and consistent all the way through.

I picked it up as a summer time pocket carry gun which I've had no problems doing with it, but I'd like to consolidate my caliber's and get something similar in 9mm. I'd like to trade for a Kel Tec PF-9, Gen 2 SCCY CPX-2, Beretta Nano, Taurus 709/740 or possibly a Kel Tec P-11 or Ruger LC9.  Might also consider a snub .38 special revolver. 

Can add 50 rounds of FMJ and 25 rounds of Hornady FTX HP's for 9mm ammo or for the right trade.  May add some cash for the right trade.
Will sell with the ammo for $260, .380 ammo isn't cheap so I'm pretty firm on the price.

I have my CCL, feel free to call/text me at three 1 six 6 one 9 nine 8 five 3 with questions or offers. Texts preferred as I sleep during the day but I will get back to you ASAP if I'm interested.
